The paper deals with the problem of developing fair classifiers using machine learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the issue of bias in classification models, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a modified gradient update step for the gradient descent-ascent algorithm, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper tests its approach on datasets and compares against state of the art algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
